  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The forthcoming book titled \"The Irish Against the War,\" published by Peter Lang Verlag in 2024, aims to address critical themes surrounding the Irish perspective on warfare. Although it currently lacks citations and online discourse, its anticipated release may spark future engagement within academic and public circles.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Scheduled for publication in 2024, \"The Irish Against the War\" seeks to illuminate the nuanced positions of Irish individuals and communities in relation to conflict. This scholarly work is positioned to contribute significantly to the discourse on war and pacifism within the context of Irish history and politics.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While it is yet to garner citations or online community engagement, the absence of these metrics at present leaves room for speculation about its potential impact. Upon release, the book may inspire discussions in academic settings, possibly influencing courses on peace studies, history, or Irish studies.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Potential readers and researchers may turn to this work to understand the historical and socio-political underpinnings of opposition to war in Ireland. Given the context of increasing global conflict, this focus could establish the work as a relevant resource for both scholars and students.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As the narrative unfolds with the book's release, the academic community may begin to explore its themes more deeply, fostering a platform for future investigations into the dynamics of Irish responses to warfare. The impact of this scholarly work, though not yet visible in current metrics, could ultimately forge connections across disciplines and stimulate broader conversations on the ethics of war.</p>",
